
[1]reticency

   RET'ICENCY, n. [L. reticentia, reticeo; re and tacco, to be silent.]

   Concealment by silence. In rhetoric, aposiopesis or suppression; a
   figure by which a person really speaks of a thing, while he makes a
   show as if he would say nothing on the subject.
